The paper focuses on convolutional neural networks (CNN) and their design for computer vision tasks, which is a core topic in computer vision (cs.CV). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of pyramid structure in CNN, which is a common technique in neural network design (cs.NE). The paper also addresses the reduction of parameters in CNN, which is a topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper evaluates the performance of the proposed method on various datasets, which is a common practice in natural language processing (cs.CL) and computer vision (cs.CV).
